<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-187-064  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 187 064.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Microprocessors and Microsystems  Dec 1989 v13 n10 p653(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Realtime digital signal processing system using a parallelprocessing architecture. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ching, P.C.; Wu, S.W.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Alow cost, high-speed, general-purpose digital signal processingsystem was constructed using the TMS32010 digital signalprocessor.andP;  The system was designed with simplicity, compactness,flexibility and expandability in mind.andP;  A parallel processingarchitecture was adopted to achieve realtime performance.andP;  Fourprocessors were used in the prototype system, but this can beexpanded easily.andP;  Interprocessor data transfer and communicationswith the host computer are facilitated via a single common bus anda bank of shared memory.andP;  A one-dimensional digital FIR filter anda realtime FFT program were used to evaluate the performance ofthe system.andP;  In addition, a realtime spectrogram was implementedas an application example.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Texas Instruments TMS32010 (Digital signal processor) (usage).andO;Topic:     Digital Signal ProcessingParallel ProcessingFast Fourier TransformsReal-Time Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Schematic block diagram of the DSP system. (chart)Block diagram of the realtime DSP. (chart)Flow diagrams of a typical application program. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>